:INFO
The Novel That Improves When You Already Know the Ending
I rated November 9 three stars the first time I read it. The central conceit, \
that Fallon and Ben agree to meet on November 9 every year for five years with \
no contact between visits, struck me as romantic but the reveal in year four \
felt manufactured. I reread it a year later and found the opposite: knowing \
the reveal changes how you read every earlier scene, and the book becomes more \
interesting, not less, when you can see where Hoover was aiming the whole time.

